HEADWORD: Tunguses
<hw>Tun*gus"es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A group of roving Turanian tribes occupying Eastern Siberia and the
<river>Amur</river> valley. They resemble the Mongols.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Tungooses</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tungusic</ent>⟦br⟧
